FBIS4-54636 "dreeu085_i_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-085 Daily Report 3 May 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serbs `Regrouping' Troops, Hardware in North Serbs `Regrouping' Troops, Hardware in North AU0305104594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 3 May 94 AU0305104594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Report by Smail Ceric from the Information Center of the 7th South Operation group] [Text] In the zone of operations of the 7th South Operations Group, the aggressor is attacking fiercely. It is constantly attacking the village of Sivsa, where there are several thousand residents. In the region of Cerovic and Omerovo Guvno, the enemy is regrouping large number of troops and hardware, which is a sign that a new offensive is being prepared. Let us hear a report: [Ceric] A general danger alarm is in force in the villages of (?Cekanica) and Djelovac. Matuzicia is real hell, because several dozens of tank and bofors shells have landed there in the last few hours. Today is marked by shelling of all defense lines.
